{
  "$schema_version": "1.1",
  "description": "Per-biomarker surface variations for the Tier 1 cutaneous melanoma biomarker panel (BRAF, NRAS, KIT, NF1, PD-L1, TMB). Weights are probabilities (floats summing to 1.0 per distribution, validated at load time). Priors seeded from TCGA SKCM, Hayward et al. Nature 2017, Cancer Genome Atlas Network Cell 2015, and targeted-sequencing meta-analyses.",
  "_changelog": [
    "v1.1: Initial melanoma panel — mirrors nsclc_adenocarcinoma schema v1.1 with cutaneous-melanoma-calibrated prevalences.",
    "BRAF: V600-dominant (~88% V600E, ~7% V600K, rare V600R/D, non-V600). Status positive 0.45 (vs ~0.025 in adenocarcinoma).",
    "NRAS: Q61-dominant (~88% of NRAS+), rare G12/G13 in cutaneous (vs mucosal). Status positive 0.20.",
    "KIT: cutaneous-melanoma rate ~5% (vs 15-20% in acral/mucosal). Exon 11 > 13 > 17.",
    "NF1: loss-of-function, heterogeneous, truncating dominant. Status positive 0.14.",
    "PD-L1: cutaneous positivity ~40%; includes MEL score alongside TPS.",
    "TMB: melanoma is canonical high-TMB disease (UV damage); status positive 0.60."
  ],
